      <section class="detail-block">
        <h2>Industry Applications</h2>
        <div class="application-tags">
          <span>SMT Production</span>
          <span>PCB Manufacturing</span>
          <span>Electronics Assembly</span>
          <span>Inspection Preparation</span>
          <span>Automated Lines</span>
        </div>
      </section>


      <section class="detail-block">
        <h2>Application Scenarios</h2>
        <div class="scenario-list">
          <div class="scenario-item">
            <h3>Pre-Solder Paste Printing PCB Cleaning</h3>
            <p>Solder paste printing is one of the most contamination-sensitive steps in SMT assembly. Dust particles on PCB pads prevent solder paste from adhering correctly, causing solder bridging, insufficient solder, or open joints after reflow. The SMT600 Series cleans both surfaces of PCBs inline before they reach the paste printer, ensuring pads are free of contamination at the most critical point in the SMT process.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="scenario-item">
            <h3>Continuous High-Volume SMT Line Cleaning</h3>
            <p>SMT production lines run continuously at high throughput, and any cleaning step that requires manual intervention or causes line stoppages reduces overall equipment effectiveness (OEE). The SMT600 Series is designed as a fully automatic inline machine with industrial PLC control, matching the continuous conveyor speed of the SMT line and eliminating the cleaning step as a production constraint.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="scenario-item">
            <h3>Component Pick-and-Place Pre-Cleaning</h3>
            <p>Before component placement, PCB surfaces must be free of particles that would prevent correct component seating or interfere with vision alignment systems on the pick-and-place machine. The SMT600 Series positioned before the pick-and-place station provides a final contamination gate that improves placement accuracy and reduces component misalignment rates.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-block">
        <h2>Designed for SMT Line Integration</h2>
        <p>The SMT600 Series is built specifically for integration into SMT production lines, not as a standalone cleaning station. The industrial PLC control system communicates with line control systems, the automatic inline conveyor matches SMT line speeds, and the dual-sided upper and lower adhesive rollers clean both PCB surfaces simultaneously without a board flip. The quick-change window structure means roller replacement takes minutes rather than hours, keeping line downtime to a minimum. For compact line layouts where floor space is limited, compare with the <a href="/products/cleaning-machine/pcb-vertical-cleaner">PCB Vertical Cleaning System</a>.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-block faq-block">
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">Where in the SMT line should the SMT600 Series be installed?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">The SMT600 Series is typically installed before the solder paste printer (pre-print) and/or before the pick-and-place machine (pre-placement). Pre-print installation is the most impactful position, as paste printing is the most contamination-sensitive step. Some lines run cleaners at both positions for maximum protection.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">Does the SMT600 clean both sides of PCBs simultaneously?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">Yes. The SMT600 Series uses dual upper and lower adhesive rollers that clean both PCB surfaces in a single pass as the board travels through the inline conveyor. This eliminates the need to flip boards and halves the cleaning time compared to single-sided machines.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">How does the PLC control system integrate with the SMT line?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">The industrial PLC communicates with the line's central control system for conveyor speed matching, start/stop synchronization, and alarm management. Contact us with your line control system specifications for integration requirements.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">What PCB sizes does the SMT600 Series support?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">PCB size compatibility is specified during machine configuration. Provide your minimum and maximum board dimensions and conveyor width requirements at the quotation stage for a correctly configured machine.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">How often does the adhesive roller need to be replaced?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">Roller replacement frequency depends on production volume, PCB surface condition, and the level of contamination being removed. The quick-change window structure is designed for fast roller access, minimizing the time taken for scheduled roller changes. Typical replacement intervals are provided based on your production specification.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">Is the SMT600 Series suitable for both leaded and lead-free SMT processes?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">Yes. The adhesive roller cleaning method is process-neutral — it removes surface particles regardless of whether the PCB is processed in a leaded or lead-free SMT line. The machine does not use water or chemicals, so there is no risk of contaminating flux systems used in either process type.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

